  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 23 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 4 critical, 9 high, 12 medium, 14 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF); plus 10 other bases. 12 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI). Network hotspots: Al Massira (AGA/GMAD), Mohammed V (CMN/GMMN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Billund (BLL/EKBI), Copenhagen Kastrup (CPH/EKCH) and 18 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Al Massira (AGA/GMAD), Mohammed V (CMN/GMMN), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and 9 others.",
